}}{{TIDTOC|adapter}} ==Overview== "8WUSG09V.0A1G" is silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos.
A MAC address (the MAC has a 00:11:95 OUI) is affixed to the back of the board in the FCC photos. :The FCC EUT's label also has a MAC on it (w/ a 00:17:9A OUI).
The FCC manual indicates that this device uses ISL3889 ([http://pccomponents.com/datasheets/CONEX06-1961BRO_PROD_CATALOG.PDF presumably CX3889]). :It is also specified as using CX3510 (PA).
The FCC test report list the following as covered models... *Alpha Networks WUS-G09V *Alpha Networks WUS-G09PB *Penbex WUGC-100 ('''Penbex''' apparently sold internet radios) *Verifone WUS-G09V
